{%- comment -%}
=============================================================================
 PRE-ORDER / INCOMING STOCK — storefront snippet (paste once)
=============================================================================

The warehouse app already does the data side automatically:
  • adds the `preorder` tag to any product that's a pre-listing or has sold out
    with stock on the way,
  • sets two metafields:
        custom.preorder_eta         (date)              e.g. 2026-07-10
        custom.preorder_ships_note  (single line text)  e.g. "Ships ~10 Jul 2026"
  • keeps the product selling at 0 stock (inventory policy = continue),
  • auto-adds it to the smart collection "Pre-order & Incoming Stock"
    (handle: preorder-incoming).

This snippet renders a clean, on-theme banner that reads the metafield and (when
the product is a pre-order) hides the theme's default "In stock" badge so the page
clearly says it's incoming. It's self-contained and inherits your theme's fonts
and colours.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 HOW TO INSTALL  (Online Store → Themes → ⋯ → Edit code, OR the theme editor)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
EASIEST (theme editor, no code):
  1. Online Store → Themes → Customize.
  2. Open a pre-order product (e.g. the Evoque fender) in the preview.
  3. On the product template, click "Add block" → "Custom Liquid" (most themes,
     incl. Dawn, have this). Drag it just under the price/availability.
  4. Paste EVERYTHING below the line marked "===== SNIPPET STARTS =====".
  5. Save. Repeat the "Add block" step once on the "Default product" template so
     all pre-order items get it.

CODE EDITOR (alternative):
  1. Edit code → Snippets → "Add a new snippet" → name it `preorder-banner`.
  2. Paste the snippet (below "===== SNIPPET STARTS =====") and Save.
  3. In your product section (e.g. sections/main-product.liquid or
     templates/product.json's main block), add near the buy button:
        {% render 'preorder-banner' %}

NOTE on hiding "In stock": the CSS below hides the most common theme availability
selectors when the product is a pre-order. If your theme still shows its own
"In stock" label, tell us the element/class and we'll add it to the hide list.
=============================================================================
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- comment -%} ===== SNIPPET STARTS ===== {%- endcomment -%}
{%- if product.tags contains 'preorder' -%}
  {%- assign po_note = product.metafields.custom.preorder_ships_note | default: 'Ships soon' -%}
  <div class="preorder-banner" role="status" style="
        margin:12px 0; padding:12px 14px; border-radius:10px;
        background:#fff8e6; border:1px solid #f0d48a; color:#7a5a00;
        font-size:14px; line-height:1.4;">
    <strong style="display:block; font-size:15px; margin-bottom:2px;">Pre-order</strong>
    {{ po_note }} — order now to reserve yours; we dispatch as soon as the stock lands.
  </div>
  <style>
    /* Hide the theme's default "in stock" availability label on pre-order pages. */
    .product__inventory,
    .product-form__inventory,
    [class*="inventory"] .in-stock,
    .product__availability,
    .availability--in-stock { display:none !important; }
  </style>
{%- endif -%}
{%- comment -%} ===== SNIPPET ENDS ===== {%- endcomment -%}
